UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669290041W
AB  - This study examines turn-of-month and pre-holiday effects on international markets. Turn-of-month effects are significant in Canada, the UK, Australia, Switzerland, and West Germany. Pre-holiday effects are significant in Canada, Japan, Hong Kong, and Australia. The absence of these effects in certain markets suggests that they originate from country-specific institutional practices. All countries exhibiting pre-holiday effects do so before local holidays; only Hong Kong does so before US holidays. This reinforces the conclusion that such anomalies are not generated solely by American institutions.
