AB  - This paper utilizes a vector autoregressive modelling technique to test which of the UK monetary aggregates (M0, M1, or £M3) is more appropriate as an intermediate target for the Bank of England. The empirical results suggest that M0 is the most suitable choice, and that £M3 is not. As to M1, the results are less straightforward, and imply that M1 may be useful for addressing policy concerns over the external balance. Other implications of the results are distilled and analyzed in the paper.
